AA.name: Debit advice
AA.desc:
Receiver of the payment message needs to return a debit advice in
                                    response to the payment message.

AB.name: Message acknowledgement
AB.desc:
Indicates that an acknowledgement relating to receipt of message is
                                    required.

AE.name: Debit advice for each transaction
AE.desc: A debit advice is requested for each transaction in the message.

AF.name: Debit advice/message acknowledgement
AF.desc:
The sender wishes to receive both a Debit Advice and an
                                    acknowledgement of receipt for a payment message.

AG.name: Authentication
AG.desc:
Authentication, by a party, of a document established for him by
                                    another party.

AH.name: Debit advice/message acknowledgement for each transaction
AH.desc:
A debit advice and message acknowledgement are requested for each
                                    transaction in the message.

AI.name: Acknowledge only changes
AI.desc: Acknowledgement of changes only is required.

AJ.name: Pending
AJ.desc:
Indication that the referenced offer or transaction (e.g. cargo
                                    booking or quotation request) is being dealt with.

AP.name: Accepted
AP.desc:
Indication that the referenced offer or transaction (e.g., cargo
                                    booking or quotation request) has been accepted.

AQ.name: Response expected
AQ.desc: The sender of the message expects a response.

AS.name: Credit advice and message acknowledgement
AS.desc:
The receiver of the message is to acknowledge receipt of the message
                                    and sent a credit advice for each credit.

CA.name: Conditionally accepted
CA.desc:
Indication that the referenced offer or transaction (e.g., cargo
                                    booking or quotation request) has been accepted under conditions indicated in this
                                    message.

CO.name: Confirmation of measurements
CO.desc:
Indication that the message contains the physical measurements on
                                    which the charges will be based.

NA.name: No acknowledgement needed
NA.desc:
Specifies that no acknowledgement is needed in response to this
                                    message.

RE.name: Rejected
RE.desc:
Indication that the referenced offer or transaction (e.g., cargo
                                    booking or quotation request) is not accepted.

UR.name: Credit advice
UR.desc:
The message recipient is to send a credit advice in response to the
                                    message.

US.name: Acknowledgement when error
US.desc: An acknowledgement is requested when an error occurred.

UT.name: Acknowledgment due to error
UT.desc:
An acknowledgment is sent because an error was identified in the
                                    received message.

UU.name: Alternate date
UU.desc:
The solution proposed in the response applies to another date than the
                                    one requested.

UV.name: Alternate service
UV.desc:
The solution proposed in the response applies to another service than
                                    the one requested.
